              <div class="row">
                <p class="col-md-12">All products are thoroughly inspected before shipment, however if upon delivery, you find an issue or defect with the item that was not listed, please contact us at <a href="customersupport@outandbackoutdoor.com">customersupport@outandbackoutdoor.com</a> for further assistance.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
  
            <div class="section purchase-location">
              <h5>What is your return policy?</h5>
              <div class="row">
                <p class="col-md-12">"We understand that sometimes you just don't fall in love with every piece of gear you buy. That's why we offer a 60 day return policy. We want to give you time to get to know your gear. And if you ultimately decide it's not meant to be, rest assured you can return items for any reason (limited exceptions* apply) within 60 days. 
                    *Gear must be returned in same condition as it was received and may not have sustained significant new damage or wear-and-tear.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
  
            <div class="section purchase-location">
              <h5>How do I return my order? </h5>
              <div class="row">
                <p class="col-md-12">"Returns can be initiated online. If you have an Out&amp;Back account, you can sign in to your profile and start a return from your orders page. If you shopped as an Out&amp;Back guest, you’ll need to access your order with your order number and email address. ALT (IF returns can't be initiated via account): Returns can be initiated by contacting our customer support team <a href="customersuuport@outandbackoutdoor.com">customersupport@outandbackoutdoor.com</a>. Please provide your order number and email address used to place your original order.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
  
            <div class="section purchase-location">
              <h5>What is Out&amp;Back's warranty on gear?</h5>
              <div class="row">
                <p class="col-md-12">Items sold on our site are built for adventure and built to last. If within the first year of ownership, you experience unusual defects or issues with your item, you will be covered by our warranty and eligible either for free repairs or store credit, depending on the specific item. For additional questions, contact <a href="customersuuport@outandbackoutdoor.com">customersupport@outandbackoutdoor.com</a>.</p>
